- What's the future?
- Despite the fact that the Kinect system has taken interaction to the physical level, a lot of interaction still happens on flat screens, sometimes in 3D.
The input flow of information has improved (the system receives more data), but the output flow has not improved much.
We're trying to change that, working on truly three-dimensional imaging systems based on different technologies, including projective.
We need to bring the computer world into our physical world, make it more real.
However, this requires knowledge not only of the user but also of the surrounding space.
Then we can add virtual objects to the real world in a much more appropriate form.
