- Of course, walking and holding the smartphone in the upper hand all the time is not very comfortable, but I think the most powerful option would be a "portable" form of augmented reality, where it would be possible to switch from glasses to smartphone, projection screen and so on at any time, based on the cloud platform.
Glasses -- it's a very personal device, and that's where their strength is (private stuff is something only you can see), and also their weakness -- augmented reality glasses don't allow you to work on virtual objects with other people at the same time.
